{
  "stem": "19198.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1933.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we were shocked, but for at least-- for the first day or two, we were not aware of the extent to which this was going to change our lives.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It took a little while to-- to find out just how serious this-- these new holders of the-- of the political power would be in the application of their crazy ideas.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- the anticipation was that, just like everybody else, once they had the responsibility of power they would act fairly normally.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we were wrong.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was 17 and 1/2.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I understood that here was a radical, right, anti-Semitic party which had gotten a bare majority in-- being in cahoots with the next most national-minded party, the [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in as much as they-- their companions were really serious and well-behaved citizens, we assumed that they would teach manners to these ruffians who had-- who had grabbed the-- the top position.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it didn't work out that way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That is, not-- not in person.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the change happened, I was in the [NON-ENGLISH], which was the [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] 11th grade of the-- of the school, the-- the high school to which I went.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And was, incidentally, the-- the top grade of the school in Eberbach.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then for the remaining two years I had to commute to Heidelberg in order to complete the 13 year course of the school.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the most visible change after-- I don't remember whether it was after a week or so, that the flag of the country was changed.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The black, red, and gold flag of the-- of the Wiemar Republic was eliminated, and the Swastika flag, black, white, and red, was hoisted in the-- in the school.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
